distanceMax.title: Distance Max
distanceMax.description: Setting this at 0 will give an infinite distance limit

inertiaFactor.title: Inertia Factor
inertiaFactor.description: Higher value means that the camera will continue moving after the user has stopped dragging. 0 is fully responsive.

focusEntity.title: Focus Entity
focusEntity.description: Entity for the camera to focus on. If blank, then the camera will use the whole scene

frameOnStart.title: Frame on Start
frameOnStart.description: Frames the entity or scene at the start of the application."

autoRender.title: Auto Render
autoRender.description: Disable to only render when camera is moving (saves power when the camera is still)

orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

capacity.title: Capacity
capacity.description: Instantiates these much elements on initialize

baseEntity.title: Base Entity
baseEntity.description: Image Element Entity that shows the base of the joystick.

nubEntity.title: Nub Entity
nubEntity.description: Image Element Entity that shows the nub (top) of the joystick.

order: Move to first touch and fixed
Move to first touch and drags

type.title: Type
type.description: Set type of behavior for the joystick.

hideOnRelease.title: Hide on Release
hideOnRelease.description: Will only show the joystick when the user is using it and will hide it on touch end. This is commonly used if you don't want the joystick to block what's being shown on screen.

identifier.title: Idenitifier
identifier.description: A unique name for the joystick to refer to it by in the API. Joysticks are also buttons so this will also be the name of button in the API. It will give a warning in browser tools if the name is not unique.

axisDeadZone.title: Axis Dead Zone
axisDeadZone.description: The number of UI units from the position of the Base Entity where input is not registered.

axisRange.title: Axis Range
axisRange.description: The number of UI units from the position of the Base Entity that the Nub Entity can move to and is the maximum range

positionOnRelease.title: Position on Release
positionOnRelease.description: Where to move the joystick on release and can help keep the screen tidy so that there are clear areas to show the game and arrange controls.

vibrationPress.title: Vibration duration (ms)
vibrationPress.description: If the device supports vibration with 'Navigator.vibrate', it will vibrate for the duration set here on touch down.Set to 0 to disable.

identifier.title: Identifier
identifier.description: A unique name for the button to refer to it by in the API. Will give a warning in browser tools if the name is not unique.

vibration.title: Vibration duration (ms)
vibration.description: If the device supports vibration with 'Navigator.vibrate', it will vibrate for the duration set here on touch down.Set to 0 to disable.

textEntity.title: Text Entity
textEntity.description: The Entity that has the text Element to update with the inputted text.

inputType.title: Input Type
inputType.description: What type of input will this field accept. On some devices, the virtual keyboard layout may change as well. For example, 'Number' will bring up a numpad instead of the full keyboard.

enterKeyHint.title: Enter Key Hint
enterKeyHint.description: Change what the enter key shows on the virutal keyboard. Different OSs will have different representations of the hint.

maxLength.title: Max Length
maxLength.description: Maximum length of the text can be.

placeHolder.title: Place Holder String
placeHolder.description: When the inputted text is empty, what should show as placeholder? Usually this is a prompt such as 'Enter your email here'.

placeHolderMobile.title: Place Holder String
placeHolderMobile.description: When the inputted text is empty, what should show as placeholder? Usually this is a prompt such as 'Enter your email here'.

placeHolderColor.title: Place Holder Text Color
placeHolderColor.description: What color the text should be when the placeholder string is used.
